Iavan Pijoos, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; Two people were critically injured on Thursday during a shooting on the opening day of the new Springs Mall on the East Rand.A community news website, the Springs Advertiser, reported that shots rang out after the ribbon-cutting ceremony.Netcare 911 spokesperson Chris Botha said there had apparently been a cash-in-transit robbery. One of the injured was airlifted to a local hospital.The mall&rsquo;s marketing manager, Amoret D&rsquo;Arrigo, said in a statement that seven suspects posing as workers entered an area under construction at the mall, and stole goods from the Incredible Connection store.D&rsquo;Arrigo said nobody was in the store at the time."We have extensive security measures in place for opening day and beyond. This includes state-of-the-art CCTV and vehicle number plate recognition, which is connected to the number plate network security initiative, in partnership with the SAPS," D&rsquo;Arrigo said.Police could not be reached for comment.Full on shooting at the opening of the Springs Mall pic.twitter.com/OZ5G7twziQ&mdash; Blakea (@RunBlakeRan) March 16, 2017Full on shooting at the opening of the Springs Mall pic.twitter.com/OZ5G7twziQRobbery in springs mall pic.twitter.com/dVjllbVFCe&mdash; Tshepo (@tshepomoswa) March 16, 2017Robbery in springs mall pic.twitter.com/dVjllbVFCe 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.